Package: anytone
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Linux CPS for Anytone D878UV / D878UV II / D578UV
 Read and write Anytone DMR codeplugs over USB, with a local Codeplug Studio
 UI (desktop WebKitGTK or browser) for editing channels, zones, APRS, GPS,
 and related settings without Windows CPS.
 .
 Supports AT-D878UV, AT-D878UV II, and AT-D578UV using reverse-engineered
 memory maps. Includes udev rules for the programming cable.
